## Phase 2 Plan: writeOutput convergence

### Goal
Converge Tier 1 commands from manual `if (flags.json) { writeJson(...) } else { format(...) }`
branching to the unified `writeOutput` helper.

### Analysis
Surveyed 11 commands (9 candidates + 2 existing callers). Found two key patterns:
1. Same data for JSON and human (rare — only org/view, issue/explain)
2. Divergent data shapes (majority — JSON gets narrowed/enriched object, human formatter needs different context)

### API Enhancement
Added to writeOutput<T, J = T>:
- `footer?: string` — collapses writeFooter() calls (3 commands had this pattern)
- `jsonData?: J` — decouples JSON serialization from human formatter data

### Migrated (3 commands)
- auth/whoami: jsonData narrows user to {id, name, username, email}
- auth/refresh: inline formatHuman replaces 3-branch if/else
- issue/explain: formatRootCauseList + footer replaces 3 separate calls

### Skipped (5 commands — don't fit writeOutput cleanly)
- issue/view, event/view, trace/view: multi-part human output (multiple formatters + span tree)
- project/create: human-only data computed after JSON early-return
- log/view: conditional single/array JSON shape + loop with separators

### Convergence Roadmap
Phase 1 (PR #373): output: "json" flag injection — DONE
Phase 2 (this PR): writeOutput convergence — DONE
Phase 3 (future): Return-based output — commands return data, wrapper handles formatting
Phase 4 (future): Format flags (--markdown, --plain, --rendered)
